1
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:31,990
[Echoes of a Thousand Moons]

2
00:01:32,060 --> 00:01:34,970
[Episode 28]

3
00:01:35,259 --> 00:01:37,890
[Wuhan, by the Yangtze River]

4
00:02:24,010 --> 00:02:24,800
Come on.

5
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:49,329
Come in, please.

6
00:03:00,790 --> 00:03:02,850
Are we still reading today, Mr. Tian?

7
00:03:03,330 --> 00:03:04,020
Of course.

8
00:03:07,730 --> 00:03:09,420
[Don Quixote]

9
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,740
Still reading "Don Quixote"?

10
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:17,520
Do you have any questions for me?

11
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,350
How are your injuries?

12
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:34,280
I'm fine. Still alive.

13
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:35,840
I'm quite lucky.

14
00:03:36,490 --> 00:03:37,520
Wanfu said

15
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:40,490
you were not injured
when you got in the car.

16
00:03:40,490 --> 00:03:41,460
He was mistaken.

17
00:03:42,390 --> 00:03:44,920
Didn't you see it yourself?
My gunshot wound.

18
00:03:45,370 --> 00:03:48,630
He only saw that I wasn't shot
outside Zengshou Restaurant.

19
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:50,840
There are plenty of people
who want me dead.

20
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:52,000
He didn't know what happened

21
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,590
on my way back in the car.

22
00:03:55,180 --> 00:03:56,780
Why did they want to kill you?

23
00:03:57,140 --> 00:03:59,400
Probably because I'm a traitor to China.

24
00:04:00,710 --> 00:04:02,120
Are you a traitor, then?

25
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:05,390
Why shouldn't I be?

26
00:04:06,570 --> 00:04:07,800
Why shouldn't I be?

27
00:04:08,420 --> 00:04:11,450
As long as you're in the Chinese district
and own a business,

28
00:04:11,450 --> 00:04:14,220
you have to abandon everything
and go to Chongqing

29
00:04:14,220 --> 00:04:16,070
to prove that you're not a traitor.

30
00:04:16,070 --> 00:04:17,570
Why am I not a traitor?

31
00:04:18,790 --> 00:04:20,589
Why must I only be a businessman?

32
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:22,190
I have so many enterprises.

33
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:23,800
I am the Boss of Tailai.

34
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:26,680
I'm not some barefoot peddler.

35
00:04:27,190 --> 00:04:29,460
I have thousands of workers
depending on me to feed them.

36
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:30,720
Can I abandon them all?

37
00:04:30,850 --> 00:04:33,380
Abandon them all
and let them starve to death?

38
00:04:37,010 --> 00:04:38,540
I don't know if you're
saying things out of anger

39
00:04:38,540 --> 00:04:40,070
or if you're being serious.

40
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,640
If you're being serious,

41
00:04:41,940 --> 00:04:43,380
then I want to resign.

42
00:04:47,159 --> 00:04:47,990
Fine.

43
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:53,240
You don't want to read for traitors.

44
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:56,330
You'd rather die than betray.
How dignified.

45
00:04:56,590 --> 00:04:57,530
Good for you.

46
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:00,720
[Don Quixote]

47
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:05,270
My husband, Zhang Yunkui,

48
00:05:05,270 --> 00:05:07,650
sacrificed his life for the country
in the Battle of Shanghai.

49
00:05:07,650 --> 00:05:08,750
My father and I

50
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:11,010
fled all the way from Nanjing to Shanghai.

51
00:05:11,010 --> 00:05:12,650
We crawled out of piles of corpses

52
00:05:12,650 --> 00:05:13,910
to make it to today.

53
00:05:14,150 --> 00:05:16,110
You have no idea what the word "traitor"

54
00:05:16,110 --> 00:05:18,220
means to us.

55
00:05:19,010 --> 00:05:21,810
We are exactly the barefoot people
you mentioned.

56
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:23,200
We are the ones you described,

57
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,360
who'd rather die than betray.

58
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:29,780
Thank you so much for the past few days

59
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,590
for giving us a roof,

60
00:05:31,620 --> 00:05:32,720
a shelter,

61
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:34,159
and a place to stay.

62
00:05:34,610 --> 00:05:35,659
I, Ding Yujiao, am

63
00:05:35,909 --> 00:05:38,760
deeply grateful for everything
you did for us before.

64
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:39,690
And from now on,

65
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,130
we won't overstay our welcome.

66
00:05:45,659 --> 00:05:48,409
I shot myself, Ding Yujiao.

67
00:05:59,590 --> 00:06:00,990
Wanfu wasn't mistaken.

68
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:06,280
Because I didn't want to join
the puppet government.

69
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:09,540
And I didn't want
the President of the Chamber of Commerce,

70
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:12,800
who already surrendered,
to keep forcing me to join them.

71
00:06:12,820 --> 00:06:14,060
I had no other choice.

72
00:06:14,270 --> 00:06:16,070
I had to shoot myself

73
00:06:17,030 --> 00:06:19,210
and tell them I was a coward,
afraid of death.

74
00:06:19,210 --> 00:06:21,360
It's not that I didn't
think of other ways.

75
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:23,650
To reclaim the factory
managed by our military,

76
00:06:23,650 --> 00:06:25,790
I begged my old classmate
of over 10 years, Kudo.

77
00:06:25,790 --> 00:06:26,720
You've seen him.

78
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:28,220
I begged for his help.

79
00:06:28,290 --> 00:06:29,680
But I was too naive.

80
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:31,820
At a time like this, as a Japanese,

81
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:33,650
how could he easily help me?

82
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,330
Over 10 years of friendship

83
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:37,950
was just my own wishful thinking.

84
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:41,580
I actually don't care at all

85
00:06:41,580 --> 00:06:43,310
whether others call me a traitor.

86
00:06:43,310 --> 00:06:44,020
And I also don't care

87
00:06:44,020 --> 00:06:46,470
whether they say
I'm a coward who's afraid of death.

88
00:06:46,470 --> 00:06:48,430
I just don't want my factory

89
00:06:48,630 --> 00:06:50,320
to produce goods

90
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,840
that support the Japanese in invading us.

91
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:53,980
What's more,

92
00:06:54,010 --> 00:06:56,080
I absolutely cannot
let my machinery factory

93
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:59,080
be converted into a Japanese arsenal
to make bullets!

94
00:06:59,650 --> 00:07:00,880
The bullets produced

95
00:07:01,060 --> 00:07:02,910
will be used to slaughter us Chinese.

96
00:07:02,910 --> 00:07:04,320
No. Absolutely not.

97
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:06,960
Not even a single bullet
shall be produced!

98
00:07:18,870 --> 00:07:20,430
Why are you telling me this?

99
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:27,440
I just don't want you
to also think I'm a traitor.

100
00:07:41,740 --> 00:07:42,730
I'm sorry.

101
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:45,440
I got you wrong.

102
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:49,920
You're not the only one who got me wrong.

103
00:07:51,260 --> 00:07:53,060
I should be the one saying sorry.

104
00:07:53,860 --> 00:07:55,190
I want to ask you a favor.

105
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,680
Please keep

106
00:07:58,220 --> 00:08:00,070
what I just said between us.

107
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:08,920
Mr. Tian,

108
00:08:09,490 --> 00:08:11,780
thank you for being honest with me.

109
00:08:11,810 --> 00:08:13,810
And also, thank you for trusting me.

110
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:17,930
Would you like to hear my story?

111
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:20,980
Go ahead, please.

112
00:08:25,950 --> 00:08:29,400
A friend of mine is
organizing a charity sale

113
00:08:29,420 --> 00:08:31,020
to raise money for refugees.

114
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:34,159
Helping those in need is

115
00:08:34,190 --> 00:08:35,940
what I have always wanted to do.

116
00:08:35,970 --> 00:08:38,190
Even if it's as small as a speck of dust,

117
00:08:38,220 --> 00:08:39,770
as long as I can help,

118
00:08:40,210 --> 00:08:41,280
I want to do it.

119
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,540
Where is the charity sale?

120
00:08:45,540 --> 00:08:47,600
In the Shanghai Career Women's Club.

121
00:08:48,090 --> 00:08:50,290
The person in charge there is my friend.

122
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:51,750
Zeng Xuefei?

123
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,450
You know her?

124
00:08:57,950 --> 00:09:00,080
When the Battle of Shanghai broke out,

125
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:02,830
I met her
at the Anti-Japanese Support Association.

126
00:09:02,830 --> 00:09:03,960
She is very capable.

127
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,130
You joined
the Anti-Japanese Support Association?

128
00:09:06,130 --> 00:09:08,890
All Shanghainese were
in the Support Association back then.

129
00:09:08,890 --> 00:09:11,220
Joining it was not something surprising.

130
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,310
Do you know her well?

131
00:09:14,690 --> 00:09:16,820
I only met her after I came to Shanghai.

132
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:19,150
She is very nice and helped me a lot.

133
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:24,580
A charity sale is a good thing,

134
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:26,910
but you also need to be careful.

135
00:09:27,890 --> 00:09:31,030
Zeng Xuefei's background...

136
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,530
But this charity sale was approved

137
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:34,040
by the Shanghai Municipal Council
in the concession.

138
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:35,500
It is compliant and legal.

139
00:09:35,610 --> 00:09:37,790
And it can also help
the concession authorities

140
00:09:37,790 --> 00:09:40,370
alleviate some refugee problems.

141
00:09:40,650 --> 00:09:43,080
After all, it is a high-profile
anti-Japanese activity.

142
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,740
The concession turns a blind eye

143
00:09:44,740 --> 00:09:46,660
to Chinese anti-Japanese activities.

144
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:48,590
But the Japanese won't sit idly by.

145
00:09:48,730 --> 00:09:51,430
At least, they will stir up trouble
and threaten you.

146
00:09:51,430 --> 00:09:54,060
At worst, they could do anything.

147
00:09:54,710 --> 00:09:57,880
I mean, do what you want to do.

148
00:09:58,210 --> 00:09:59,850
But you still need to be shrewd

149
00:09:59,850 --> 00:10:01,580
and learn to protect yourself.

150
00:10:06,820 --> 00:10:08,300
Thank you, Mr. Tian.

151
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:11,520
It's just that from now on,

152
00:10:13,650 --> 00:10:16,250
no one will read to me anymore.

153
00:10:23,690 --> 00:10:26,590
[Don Quixote]

154
00:10:30,570 --> 00:10:34,290
Before, it was a resignation.

155
00:10:34,420 --> 00:10:35,350
Now,

156
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:37,810
it's taking a leave,

157
00:10:37,810 --> 00:10:39,020
if you agree.

158
00:10:42,690 --> 00:10:43,590
Thank you.

159
00:10:46,710 --> 00:10:47,950
Still "Don Quixote"?

160
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:48,840
Yes, of course.

161
00:10:48,990 --> 00:10:51,400
Then, let's start
from where the bookmark is.

162
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,260
Yes, of course.

163
00:10:57,410 --> 00:10:59,340
"Covering himself with his shield

164
00:10:59,740 --> 00:11:02,160
and putting his lance in the rest,

165
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:04,620
he urged Rocinante forward

166
00:11:04,990 --> 00:11:07,120
to attack the windmill up ahead.

167
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:11,940
But as he thrust his lance
into the windmill's sail,

168
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:14,550
the wind turned it with such violence

169
00:11:14,570 --> 00:11:17,470
that it shattered his lance to pieces."

170
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:22,500
"The wild geese fly.

171
00:11:22,790 --> 00:11:24,320
Their wings are whirring."

172
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:27,430
"The autumn wild geese
fly 1,000 miles in the wind.

173
00:11:27,430 --> 00:11:30,430
We can toast merrily to such a sight
in the high tower."

174
00:11:33,090 --> 00:11:33,880
Yufeng,

175
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,850
your mindset is
much more optimistic than mine.

176
00:11:37,210 --> 00:11:38,490
I have experienced

177
00:11:38,510 --> 00:11:39,770
harder days than this.

178
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:42,330
You have experienced harder days?

179
00:11:42,630 --> 00:11:44,320
You call it the Long March.

180
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,200
That's right, the Long March.

181
00:11:47,470 --> 00:11:49,070
Here you are, Commissar Xie.

182
00:11:49,310 --> 00:11:50,040
Yunkui.

183
00:11:51,380 --> 00:11:52,220
Thank you.

184
00:11:53,070 --> 00:11:54,110
Okay, thanks.

185
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,200
But fortunately,

186
00:12:01,870 --> 00:12:03,770
the days of Chinese fighting Chinese

187
00:12:03,770 --> 00:12:04,650
are over.

188
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:07,420
I believe things
will get better and better.

189
00:12:09,290 --> 00:12:10,490
They will get better.

190
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:12,650
What are your plans next?

191
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:17,590
They are marching
to the Southern Anhui Base,

192
00:12:17,590 --> 00:12:19,760
and I am heading
to the Hubei-Henan border.

193
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:21,500
Are you going behind enemy lines alone?

194
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:22,380
I'm used to it.

195
00:12:23,060 --> 00:12:25,580
Like a wandering monk, a lone ranger.

196
00:12:28,930 --> 00:12:29,640
And you?

197
00:12:32,330 --> 00:12:33,490
I have nowhere to go.

198
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:42,480
Yunkui,

199
00:12:43,870 --> 00:12:45,260
I heard from Zuliang

200
00:12:46,220 --> 00:12:48,550
that you fought in the Battle of Shanghai.

201
00:12:51,870 --> 00:12:52,800
I did.

202
00:12:54,330 --> 00:12:55,190
What about you?

203
00:12:55,830 --> 00:12:59,630
I guess it was also not your first time
fighting the Japanese, right?

204
00:13:00,180 --> 00:13:01,910
During the Battle of Shanghai,

205
00:13:02,150 --> 00:13:03,950
I was in Shanghai the whole time.

206
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:08,050
In the early stage, I contacted
my old friends and built a core team.

207
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:11,990
Later, I organized guerrillas
in the suburbs.

208
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:15,770
Not until the end of last year
was I transferred to Wuhan.

209
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,050
Yufeng,

210
00:13:17,710 --> 00:13:21,110
what do you think
of the Battle of Shanghai?

211
00:13:24,710 --> 00:13:25,950
To be honest?

212
00:13:25,980 --> 00:13:27,910
Of course, I want to hear the truth.

213
00:13:30,010 --> 00:13:33,190
Actually, Shanghai is just
a small peninsula

214
00:13:33,430 --> 00:13:36,630
between Hangzhou Bay
and the Yangtze River Estuary.

215
00:13:37,620 --> 00:13:40,200
In such an area,
densely covered with waterways,

216
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:43,360
flat, narrow, and with shallow depth,

217
00:13:43,780 --> 00:13:46,310
you deployed 700,000 elite soldiers
right from the start

218
00:13:46,310 --> 00:13:49,140
to fight a head-on decisive battle
with the enemy.

219
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:51,580
With all due respect, Yunkui,

220
00:13:52,150 --> 00:13:53,870
I think this in itself was

221
00:13:54,590 --> 00:13:57,050
a reckless and dangerous strategic policy.

222
00:13:57,540 --> 00:13:59,310
It's a replica of the KMT Army's
"encirclement and suppression" campaigns

223
00:13:59,310 --> 00:14:00,890
against the Red Army
and the civil war mindset.

224
00:14:00,890 --> 00:14:04,640
But facing the deep, long assaults
by the Japanese Army's

225
00:14:04,670 --> 00:14:06,410
mechanized troops,

226
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:08,860
this was completely wrong.

227
00:14:09,660 --> 00:14:13,460
The Battle of Shanghai failed
because of a lack of strategic vision.

228
00:14:13,910 --> 00:14:16,190
We had the advantage of striking first,

229
00:14:16,210 --> 00:14:19,130
taking the initiative
before the Japanese Army deployed,

230
00:14:19,130 --> 00:14:21,660
but it was just a piecemeal tactic.

231
00:14:23,170 --> 00:14:24,770
We had no profound awareness

232
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:26,710
of all the reactions of the Japanese Army.

233
00:14:26,710 --> 00:14:28,510
With the Japanese mobile troops

234
00:14:28,910 --> 00:14:30,400
landing from the flank,

235
00:14:30,420 --> 00:14:31,590
the KMT Army

236
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:34,750
was utterly routed
with no strategic passes to defend.

237
00:14:34,750 --> 00:14:36,140
Under these circumstances,

238
00:14:36,140 --> 00:14:38,070
no matter how many troops were deployed,

239
00:14:38,070 --> 00:14:40,770
we could only be defeated one by one,

240
00:14:40,870 --> 00:14:42,540
leaving only the retreat to Nanjing.

241
00:14:42,540 --> 00:14:45,220
There was neither
an in-depth echelon configuration

242
00:14:45,220 --> 00:14:47,510
nor anti-assault reserves.

243
00:14:47,530 --> 00:14:50,820
The frontline was deployed too long
and too close to the water,

244
00:14:50,820 --> 00:14:54,000
only increasing casualties
under the bombing of Japanese naval guns.

245
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,260
As for the second-line troops,

246
00:14:55,260 --> 00:14:57,110
they couldn't reinforce the frontline,

247
00:14:57,110 --> 00:15:01,090
and they failed to form
a pincer movement with each other.

248
00:15:01,170 --> 00:15:02,880
This directly gave the Japanese Army

249
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:05,810
great opportunities to divide, surround,

250
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:07,530
and annihilate your forces.

251
00:15:07,820 --> 00:15:10,750
Moreover, after the defense system
was fragmented,

252
00:15:11,310 --> 00:15:14,610
the reinforcements only arrived
in dribs and drabs slowly,

253
00:15:14,610 --> 00:15:16,920
failing to organize
a powerful counterattack.

254
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:18,510
This further led to the defenders

255
00:15:18,510 --> 00:15:21,370
being tightly pinned down
by the Japanese Army, unable to escape.

256
00:15:21,370 --> 00:15:23,720
Ultimately, it turned into isolated fights

257
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:26,180
city by city, place by place,
with no choice.

258
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:27,390
From my perspective,

259
00:15:27,390 --> 00:15:30,790
there was a lack
of highly effective tactical coordination.

260
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:33,520
There was no air-ground coordination.

261
00:15:33,750 --> 00:15:37,390
Also, the coordination
between the infantry's artillery and tanks

262
00:15:37,390 --> 00:15:39,120
was almost non-existent.

263
00:15:39,790 --> 00:15:40,710
At that time,

264
00:15:40,730 --> 00:15:42,990
everyone was fighting
their own battles and charging blindly

265
00:15:42,990 --> 00:15:44,350
like a sheet of loose sand.

266
00:15:44,350 --> 00:15:46,430
But the Japanese were

267
00:15:46,590 --> 00:15:47,940
the exact opposite in this respect.

268
00:15:47,940 --> 00:15:49,190
All their actions

269
00:15:49,220 --> 00:15:51,280
aligned like a highly precise clock.

270
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:53,560
All their coordination was very organic

271
00:15:53,580 --> 00:15:54,980
without even a second of error.

272
00:15:54,980 --> 00:15:56,310
But what about our army?

273
00:15:56,820 --> 00:15:59,000
Once an attack was blocked at one point,

274
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,740
we could only rely on soldiers
charging forward.

275
00:16:00,740 --> 00:16:01,980
What was the use of that?

276
00:16:01,980 --> 00:16:03,380
Charging forward just meant death.

277
00:16:03,380 --> 00:16:05,150
This resulted in massive casualties.

278
00:16:05,150 --> 00:16:07,880
We sent a whole division,
and in less than a day...

279
00:16:10,550 --> 00:16:13,010
In less than a day,
everyone was sacrificed.

280
00:16:18,740 --> 00:16:22,270
The loyalty and bravery
of the soldiers are heroic and moving.

281
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:26,760
But then again, after this battle,

282
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:29,050
your elite main forces were
completely crushed,

283
00:16:29,050 --> 00:16:31,150
directly leading to the fall of Nanjing.

284
00:16:31,150 --> 00:16:34,280
The Japanese Army marched
deep into the Central Plains.

285
00:16:34,390 --> 00:16:36,450
I was in the countryside at that time.

286
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:40,150
Looking around,
there were stragglers all over,

287
00:16:40,170 --> 00:16:43,630
abandoning their armor and weapons.
It was a miserable sight.

288
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:45,400
How innocent the people were!

289
00:16:46,050 --> 00:16:49,170
Some fled, some resisted,

290
00:16:49,820 --> 00:16:51,090
and some were robbed.

291
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:53,670
To be honest, Yunkui,

292
00:16:54,420 --> 00:16:55,550
when I saw all this,

293
00:16:55,570 --> 00:16:57,510
it was completely a state of anarchy.

294
00:16:57,510 --> 00:16:59,470
I had only one thought in my mind.

295
00:17:00,380 --> 00:17:02,680
I thought, "The future of China

296
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:04,569
must not be entrusted

297
00:17:04,589 --> 00:17:06,109
to such commanders.

298
00:17:06,540 --> 00:17:08,690
If we fight the war of resistance
this way, like loose sand,

299
00:17:08,690 --> 00:17:10,359
China will be doomed."

300
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:16,380
After the Battle of Wuhan,

301
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:19,400
the top priority of the Japanese Army
is not to continue marching west,

302
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:22,060
but to occupy as many coastal areas
as possible.

303
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:22,790
Their purpose

304
00:17:22,790 --> 00:17:24,750
is to cut off our maritime supply lines.

305
00:17:24,750 --> 00:17:26,640
This would plunge us into a state

306
00:17:26,660 --> 00:17:27,930
of isolation and helplessness,

307
00:17:27,930 --> 00:17:30,030
forcing us to finally give up resistance.

308
00:17:30,030 --> 00:17:31,870
They intend to wear down the KMT's Army,

309
00:17:31,870 --> 00:17:33,310
disintegrate the will of the high command,

310
00:17:33,310 --> 00:17:35,550
and even sow discord among them.

311
00:17:35,940 --> 00:17:38,360
At the same time,
they are concentrating forces

312
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:41,040
to suppress resistance forces
in the occupied areas,

313
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:43,880
such as the Eighth Route Army
and the New Fourth Army.

314
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:46,010
Only by destroying these vital forces

315
00:17:46,110 --> 00:17:47,180
can they extract more

316
00:17:47,180 --> 00:17:48,660
of all the resources in the occupied areas

317
00:17:48,660 --> 00:17:49,480
to make up

318
00:17:49,510 --> 00:17:51,570
for Japan's ailing wartime economy.

319
00:17:51,730 --> 00:17:52,810
Am I right?

320
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:55,010
I'm impressed, Yunkui.

321
00:17:55,780 --> 00:17:58,130
Your view is exactly the same as ours.

322
00:17:59,260 --> 00:18:00,640
I sincerely invite you

323
00:18:00,690 --> 00:18:02,690
to the Army Headquarters
of the New Fourth Army

324
00:18:02,690 --> 00:18:04,120
in Yunling, Anhui, for a visit.

325
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:05,320
What do you think?

326
00:18:08,260 --> 00:18:09,100
Yufeng,

327
00:18:09,650 --> 00:18:11,060
thank you for your kindness.

328
00:18:11,060 --> 00:18:13,130
And the words you just told me

329
00:18:13,530 --> 00:18:14,850
have inspired me a lot.

330
00:18:15,230 --> 00:18:17,010
I want to explore and adventure on my own,

331
00:18:17,010 --> 00:18:18,290
to be a wandering monk,

332
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:20,790
to be a lone ranger.

333
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:23,100
My ancestral home is Haiwen.

334
00:18:23,130 --> 00:18:26,080
I want to go back to Haiwen,

335
00:18:26,430 --> 00:18:28,310
try to contact my old acquaintances,

336
00:18:28,310 --> 00:18:31,440
and develop an independent
anti-Japanese armed force.

337
00:18:31,750 --> 00:18:32,590
Good luck.

338
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:45,090
Where are the potatoes?

339
00:18:47,930 --> 00:18:49,450
I remember I packed them.

340
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:53,030
Here, eat this.

341
00:18:57,140 --> 00:18:58,070
Thanks, Sis.

342
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:01,030
Here you are.

343
00:19:06,220 --> 00:19:07,060
Ms. Fu Fan,

344
00:19:07,490 --> 00:19:10,210
why were you and Commissar Xie

345
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:11,840
walking in circles just now?

346
00:19:12,950 --> 00:19:15,730
Were you trying to confirm with each other

347
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:17,810
if you had any injuries?

348
00:19:19,060 --> 00:19:21,190
See it through, but don't point it out.

349
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:24,750
Buddy,

350
00:19:24,780 --> 00:19:26,910
I haven't washed my feet in a long time.

351
00:19:26,940 --> 00:19:28,870
Even I myself find the smell disgusting.

352
00:19:28,870 --> 00:19:30,360
Sorry for making you suffer.

353
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:31,320
This is nothing.

354
00:19:31,380 --> 00:19:33,400
I've smelled all kinds of ordour
on the battlefield.

355
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:34,330
It's fine.

356
00:19:35,850 --> 00:19:37,150
Back at the steel mill,

357
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:39,000
you said I'd die when the boat arrived.

358
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,400
Aren't we all fine getting here by boat?

359
00:19:41,420 --> 00:19:43,570
The fortune teller said I've got 9 lives.

360
00:19:43,570 --> 00:19:44,700
I didn't die, right?

361
00:19:49,090 --> 00:19:49,920
Give it a try.

362
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:54,010
What do you mean?

363
00:20:03,520 --> 00:20:04,630
You're so amazing!

364
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:08,500
You've got some skills.

365
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:10,670
Yufeng,

366
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:13,750
I have another question for you.

367
00:20:14,690 --> 00:20:15,480
Go ahead.

368
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:20,020
Chairman Mao Zedong
of your party once said,

369
00:20:20,050 --> 00:20:23,180
"The army and the people are
the foundation of victory."

370
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:25,400
How should this sentence be interpreted?

371
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:28,050
When I was studying
at Yan'an Counter-Japanese University,

372
00:20:28,050 --> 00:20:29,850
Chairman Mao told us something.

373
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:32,110
What is a real impregnable bastion?

374
00:20:32,850 --> 00:20:33,810
It is the masses.

375
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:35,250
It's the millions upon millions

376
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:38,320
of masses who genuinely
and sincerely support the revolution.

377
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:40,450
They are the real impregnable bastion

378
00:20:40,850 --> 00:20:42,770
that no force can smash.

379
00:20:43,010 --> 00:20:45,580
The 400 million people unite as one,

380
00:20:45,820 --> 00:20:48,440
with both the army
and the people carrying forward

381
00:20:48,440 --> 00:20:50,230
the conscious initiative in the war.

382
00:20:50,230 --> 00:20:51,430
This unity lays

383
00:20:51,460 --> 00:20:53,330
the most fundamental foundation
for victory in the War

384
00:20:53,330 --> 00:20:55,080
of Resistance Against Japanese Aggression.

385
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:56,970
Mobilize the people across the country

386
00:20:56,970 --> 00:20:57,700
to gather

387
00:20:57,730 --> 00:21:00,440
into a vast ocean that drowns the enemy.

388
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:03,470
Only a war fully relying on the people

389
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:05,720
can achieve final victory.

390
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:10,750
I really envy you.

391
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:12,970
Ms. Fu Fan,

392
00:21:13,550 --> 00:21:16,920
are there many female soldiers
in your New Fourth Army?

393
00:21:17,040 --> 00:21:17,680
Yes.

394
00:21:17,890 --> 00:21:20,550
Then, if I want to join
you in the New Fourth Army,

395
00:21:20,760 --> 00:21:22,680
do I have to cut my braid?

396
00:21:23,270 --> 00:21:24,480
We have a rule.

397
00:21:24,840 --> 00:21:26,390
All must have bobbed hair.

398
00:21:27,360 --> 00:21:29,610
We also have a ballad.

399
00:21:29,740 --> 00:21:31,700
The lyrics go like this.

400
00:21:32,380 --> 00:21:34,220
"No bound feet, no coiled hair.

401
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:36,580
Cut a bob and become a red soldier.

402
00:21:37,370 --> 00:21:40,860
Follow the army to reclaim the land."

403
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:43,820
If I want to be a female soldier
in the New Fourth Army,

404
00:21:43,820 --> 00:21:45,420
are there any requirements?

405
00:21:45,980 --> 00:21:46,930
Xiaoyue,

406
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,920
anyone with a patriotic heart is

407
00:21:49,940 --> 00:21:51,220
welcome to join us.

408
00:21:52,870 --> 00:21:54,380
In our current ranks,

409
00:21:55,170 --> 00:21:58,900
we have people from Jiangxi, Anhui,

410
00:21:59,070 --> 00:22:00,550
Jiangsu, and Shandong.

411
00:22:00,570 --> 00:22:02,480
They're from all over the country.

412
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:07,810
Some of them were maids
working for landlords before,

413
00:22:07,940 --> 00:22:10,740
some were oppressed female workers,

414
00:22:10,940 --> 00:22:11,940
and some fled from arranged marriages.

415
00:22:11,940 --> 00:22:14,340
Of course, there are also female students.

416
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:16,350
They come from all walks of life.

417
00:22:17,690 --> 00:22:19,450
What did you do before?

418
00:22:21,020 --> 00:22:23,290
I was a primary school teacher.

419
00:22:23,770 --> 00:22:26,560
I taught kids to read and sing.

420
00:22:27,430 --> 00:22:28,280
Sing?

421
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:32,300
Then you must be a good singer.

422
00:22:32,650 --> 00:22:35,410
Sing us a song. Come on.

423
00:22:41,130 --> 00:22:41,860
Comrades,

424
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:44,190
we are about to set off.

425
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:46,030
I'll sing a song for you

426
00:22:46,050 --> 00:22:47,830
to cheer us up
and relieve our fatigue, alright?

427
00:22:47,830 --> 00:22:49,000
-Okay!
-Nice!

428
00:22:49,170 --> 00:22:50,570
Sing along if you can.

429
00:22:53,030 --> 00:22:58,460
♪ The Great Wall is 10,000 li long ♪

430
00:22:58,640 --> 00:23:03,560
♪ Outside the Great Wall is my hometown ♪

431
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:08,960
♪ Plump sorghum, fragrant soybeans ♪

432
00:23:09,150 --> 00:23:13,710
♪ Fields like gold, with few disasters ♪

433
00:23:14,440 --> 00:23:19,310
♪ Since the calamity struck ♪

434
00:23:19,590 --> 00:23:25,240
♪ Rape and pillage have brought
unbearable suffering ♪

435
00:23:25,590 --> 00:23:30,830
♪ Due to unbearable suffering,
we fled elsewhere ♪

436
00:23:31,030 --> 00:23:35,350
♪ Families were scattered;
parents died ♪

437
00:23:36,310 --> 00:23:38,170
After we drive the Japanese away,

438
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:40,640
what do you want to do?

439
00:23:42,870 --> 00:23:43,510
Me?

440
00:23:46,750 --> 00:23:48,180
I'm going to say it,
but don't laugh at me.

441
00:23:48,180 --> 00:23:48,980
Okay. Tell me.

442
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:52,240
I want to be a newspaper journalist.

443
00:23:52,590 --> 00:23:54,200
I really like photography.

444
00:23:54,820 --> 00:23:55,950
When the time comes,

445
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:59,270
I want to buy a good camera

446
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:02,770
and travel across
the country's famous landscapes.

447
00:24:04,270 --> 00:24:07,470
"Steeds gallop in the autumn wind
north of the Great Wall.

448
00:24:08,260 --> 00:24:11,330
Apricot flowers bloom in the misty rain
south of the Yangtze River."

449
00:24:11,330 --> 00:24:14,250
I'd like to record this heroic era.

450
00:24:15,390 --> 00:24:16,220
How about you?

451
00:24:17,220 --> 00:24:18,220
I like machinery.

452
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:20,310
I want to build a car myself.

453
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:23,030
When there's no more war in the future,

454
00:24:23,030 --> 00:24:25,500
weapons are stored,
and swords are turned into plowshares.

455
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:26,740
I also want to go see

456
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:30,240
"the bright moon rising from the sea;
the moonlight surging in river torrents."

457
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:33,070
I want to experience
"the straight smoke in the vast desert;

458
00:24:33,070 --> 00:24:35,470
the round setting sun
over the long river."

459
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:36,910
Magnificent.

460
00:24:37,730 --> 00:24:38,640
Magnificent.

461
00:24:40,830 --> 00:24:45,920
♪ The Great Wall is 10,000 li long ♪

462
00:24:46,070 --> 00:24:51,790
♪ Outside the Great Wall is my hometown ♪

463
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:57,090
♪ Four hundred million compatriots are
united as one ♪

464
00:24:57,270 --> 00:25:03,440
♪ The new Great Wall is 10,000 li long ♪

465
00:25:03,740 --> 00:25:05,060
Have pity, please.

466
00:25:06,150 --> 00:25:07,950
I haven't had any food for 3 days.

467
00:25:08,490 --> 00:25:10,220
Please show mercy.

468
00:25:10,240 --> 00:25:11,700
I haven't eaten for 3 days.

469
00:25:12,620 --> 00:25:13,680
Have pity, please.

470
00:25:15,270 --> 00:25:16,590
Eat it. It's not dirty.

471
00:25:16,940 --> 00:25:18,540
Thank you, thank you so much.

472
00:25:22,390 --> 00:25:23,850
You said I was thoughtful.

473
00:25:24,860 --> 00:25:27,010
I think you're quite thoughtful, too.

474
00:25:30,110 --> 00:25:31,070
Read books?

475
00:25:31,520 --> 00:25:33,670
You have her read for you again and again.

476
00:25:33,670 --> 00:25:35,150
Screw you.

477
00:25:44,680 --> 00:25:45,750
What are you doing?

478
00:25:45,860 --> 00:25:47,180
What do you want?

479
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:48,880
What are you up to?

480
00:25:49,310 --> 00:25:50,680
I just have that much money!

481
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:52,250
It's my grocery money!

482
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:53,420
Take it all!

483
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:54,440
Just take it all!

484
00:25:54,470 --> 00:25:55,860
Sir, spare my life!

485
00:25:55,890 --> 00:25:57,350
Sir, please spare my life!

486
00:26:03,820 --> 00:26:05,270
Sir, I beg you to spare my life.

487
00:26:05,270 --> 00:26:08,400
Spare my life. Please spare my life.

488
00:26:09,480 --> 00:26:10,160
Turn around.

489
00:26:10,160 --> 00:26:11,910
I won't turn around! I won't!

490
00:26:11,940 --> 00:26:13,520
Sir, I didn't see your face.

491
00:26:13,550 --> 00:26:15,850
You won't kill me
if I didn't see your face.

492
00:26:15,850 --> 00:26:16,920
Sir, please let me go.

493
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:17,920
Let me go back, please.

494
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:19,530
I didn't see your face anyway.

495
00:26:19,530 --> 00:26:20,740
Please spare me.

496
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:23,090
Let me go. Please let me go.

497
00:26:24,030 --> 00:26:26,510
Turn around and look up at me.

498
00:26:26,540 --> 00:26:28,410
I won't turn around! I won't look up!

499
00:26:28,410 --> 00:26:29,930
I won't look at you!

500
00:26:30,370 --> 00:26:31,630
You coward.

501
00:26:31,790 --> 00:26:34,830
I'll give you 3 pieces of advice for free,

502
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:36,640
Kong Erbao.

503
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:47,170
Blindy?

504
00:26:48,680 --> 00:26:49,750
To the Brigade Commander.

505
00:26:49,750 --> 00:26:51,150
To Company Commander Yu.

506
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:52,510
To Platoon Leader Wang.

507
00:26:52,540 --> 00:26:53,490
To Tieta.

508
00:26:53,640 --> 00:26:54,830
To Wu Youcai!

509
00:26:54,850 --> 00:26:55,860
To Xiu!

510
00:26:56,310 --> 00:26:59,590
To the 49 soldiers who died in Liu Town.

511
00:26:59,670 --> 00:27:01,560
To all the soldiers of our brigade

512
00:27:02,480 --> 00:27:06,110
who died in Shanghai.

513
00:27:06,130 --> 00:27:06,670
Cheers.

514
00:27:17,380 --> 00:27:20,510
Huang, you're still alive.

515
00:27:21,400 --> 00:27:22,980
And I'm still alive, too.

516
00:27:26,570 --> 00:27:29,600
Should I call you Kong Erbao

517
00:27:29,730 --> 00:27:31,060
or Meng Wanfu?

518
00:27:34,260 --> 00:27:35,820
Meng Wanfu, Meng Wanfu.

519
00:27:35,850 --> 00:27:37,700
Meng Wanfu, 100% genuine.

520
00:27:40,330 --> 00:27:41,760
Then, Meng Wanfu,

521
00:27:41,790 --> 00:27:45,280
why did you take
the Brigade Commander's wife and father

522
00:27:45,300 --> 00:27:49,600
to live
in the Traitor Tian Jiatai's house?

523
00:27:50,070 --> 00:27:51,590
It's a long story.

524
00:27:52,070 --> 00:27:54,270
Anyway, it was all to keep
the 3 of them alive.

525
00:27:54,270 --> 00:27:56,610
Then the Brigade Commander's wife

526
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:58,720
ended up playing my wife.

527
00:27:58,940 --> 00:28:01,150
His father became my father.

528
00:28:01,170 --> 00:28:03,250
His son became my son.

529
00:28:03,790 --> 00:28:06,210
Anyway, it's just been a mess

530
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:07,700
and ended up like this now.

531
00:28:09,310 --> 00:28:11,610
Then how did the Brigade Commander's wife

532
00:28:11,610 --> 00:28:14,070
have an affair
with the Traitor Tian Jiatai?

533
00:28:14,790 --> 00:28:15,470
Bullshit!

534
00:28:15,500 --> 00:28:16,790
Why are you talking bullshit?

535
00:28:16,790 --> 00:28:18,800
Who told you they were having an affair?

536
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:19,750
Call the rumor mongers over here.

537
00:28:19,750 --> 00:28:20,820
I'll beat them up.

538
00:28:21,270 --> 00:28:22,130
What about you?

539
00:28:22,550 --> 00:28:25,060
I saw you stay with her every day.

540
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:27,390
What nonsense are you talking about?

541
00:28:27,390 --> 00:28:29,120
We're a fake couple, of course.

542
00:28:29,560 --> 00:28:31,640
I have Xiaoyue, and you know that!

543
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:34,510
And I know Xiaoyue is in Wuhan.

544
00:28:34,830 --> 00:28:36,000
I have to take care

545
00:28:36,020 --> 00:28:37,360
of the Brigade Commander's family of 3,

546
00:28:37,360 --> 00:28:38,710
so I've been staying in Shanghai

547
00:28:38,710 --> 00:28:40,710
and haven't gone to look for her yet.

548
00:28:42,790 --> 00:28:44,570
Oh, Wanfu.

549
00:28:44,700 --> 00:28:46,860
You were at death's door

550
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:48,410
without even realizing it.

551
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:52,420
What happened to me?

552
00:28:52,420 --> 00:28:54,940
What happened? You were almost wiped out.

553
00:28:55,370 --> 00:28:56,880
Thankfully, I thought you looked familiar,

554
00:28:56,880 --> 00:28:58,480
so I tied you up to take a look first.

555
00:28:58,480 --> 00:28:59,550
Otherwise you...

556
00:29:03,500 --> 00:29:06,030
You were the ones
who fired the shots that day?

557
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:12,070
Wanfu,

558
00:29:12,530 --> 00:29:16,290
you are a righteous and brave man.

559
00:29:16,950 --> 00:29:19,590
You saved the Brigade Commander's wife,

560
00:29:19,610 --> 00:29:21,710
father, and son several times.

561
00:29:21,740 --> 00:29:23,800
You have taken care of them until now.

562
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:29,600
I, Huang Ziming, sincerely express
my gratitude to you.

563
00:29:30,950 --> 00:29:32,200
I'm so grateful.

564
00:29:32,220 --> 00:29:33,700
Wait, Blindy, I...

565
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:35,630
I don't understand you now.

566
00:29:35,630 --> 00:29:37,130
Which side exactly are you on?

567
00:29:37,130 --> 00:29:38,340
Which side do I look like I'm on?

568
00:29:38,340 --> 00:29:39,520
Stop pretending to be mysterious.

569
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:40,640
I don't care which side you're on.

570
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:42,210
What exactly do you do now?

571
00:29:42,230 --> 00:29:43,900
What have you been through this past year

572
00:29:43,900 --> 00:29:45,600
to become like this?

573
00:29:48,320 --> 00:29:50,710
Sit, sit. Sit down now.

574
00:29:53,910 --> 00:29:54,950
Liu Town.

575
00:29:55,310 --> 00:29:57,850
I was lucky in that battle in Liu Town.

576
00:29:57,870 --> 00:29:59,600
The Lord of Hell didn't take me.

577
00:30:01,570 --> 00:30:04,170
The next day, I woke up.

578
00:30:04,190 --> 00:30:06,030
I must have been knocked out.

579
00:30:06,340 --> 00:30:09,250
I woke up and went to look for you,

580
00:30:11,960 --> 00:30:13,310
but you were all gone.

581
00:30:14,730 --> 00:30:16,380
I crawled out of Liu Town

582
00:30:16,750 --> 00:30:18,840
and met an officer from BIS.

583
00:30:19,320 --> 00:30:21,490
He said I had strong adaptability,

584
00:30:22,530 --> 00:30:24,240
and there was a place better suited for me

585
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:25,970
than the battlefield.

586
00:30:27,010 --> 00:30:30,060
I followed him to Hongkou.

587
00:30:30,750 --> 00:30:34,280
Later, the BIS higher-ups found me again

588
00:30:34,790 --> 00:30:36,990
and sent me to Jiangxi

589
00:30:37,230 --> 00:30:39,160
for formal training.

590
00:30:39,930 --> 00:30:41,360
Not long ago,

591
00:30:41,390 --> 00:30:43,280
I was sent back to Shanghai

592
00:30:43,300 --> 00:30:45,140
to be specifically in charge

593
00:30:46,410 --> 00:30:49,250
of eliminating traitors and defectors.

594
00:30:49,510 --> 00:30:52,670
What... What have you done?

595
00:30:56,550 --> 00:30:59,150
The anniversary
of the Lugou Bridge Incident.

596
00:31:00,690 --> 00:31:02,740
That explosion was your doing?

597
00:31:03,060 --> 00:31:04,580
But I heard

598
00:31:04,610 --> 00:31:06,740
that only 2 Japanese were killed,

599
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:08,830
and 2 Chinese died as well.

600
00:31:10,140 --> 00:31:13,620
Wanfu, when looking at a matter,

601
00:31:13,820 --> 00:31:16,750
you have to understand
its significance and impact.

602
00:31:19,990 --> 00:31:22,780
I... I understand. I got it.

603
00:31:24,030 --> 00:31:25,750
You don't need to know that much.

604
00:31:25,750 --> 00:31:26,790
Wanfu,

605
00:31:26,810 --> 00:31:30,530
it's so good to see you today.

606
00:31:31,590 --> 00:31:34,600
Half-Immortal Huang, Blind Huang.

607
00:31:37,790 --> 00:31:40,610
You are alive, and I am alive.

608
00:31:41,600 --> 00:31:42,640
That is good.

609
00:31:44,310 --> 00:31:45,280
That is good.

610
00:31:48,630 --> 00:31:50,340
Your current position in the Tian Mansion

611
00:31:50,340 --> 00:31:52,800
is very favourable for us.
That is also good.

612
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:56,160
Mr. Tian is not a traitor.

613
00:31:56,850 --> 00:31:59,250
Blindy,
you tried to kill the wrong person.

614
00:32:00,150 --> 00:32:01,780
Tian Jiatai is not a traitor?

615
00:32:02,370 --> 00:32:04,200
He is an industrialist.

616
00:32:04,640 --> 00:32:06,260
He accumulated blessings in his past life,

617
00:32:06,260 --> 00:32:08,860
so he deserves to be rich
in this life, you know?

618
00:32:09,510 --> 00:32:12,650
Yes, I know he has dealings
with the Japanese.

619
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:14,670
But that person is not a Japanese soldier.

620
00:32:14,670 --> 00:32:16,070
He is his college classmate.

621
00:32:16,070 --> 00:32:17,440
What's his title again?

622
00:32:18,260 --> 00:32:19,830
An e-economics professor.

623
00:32:20,680 --> 00:32:21,540
Think about it.

624
00:32:21,590 --> 00:32:23,680
If he had no dealings with the Japanese,

625
00:32:23,680 --> 00:32:25,190
how could he get
the police station to release

626
00:32:25,190 --> 00:32:28,050
the Brigade Commander's father
with just one call?

627
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,960
If Tian Jiatai weren't a traitor to China,

628
00:32:31,960 --> 00:32:34,420
then there would be no traitors
in Shanghai.

629
00:32:34,500 --> 00:32:37,430
Wanfu, you still
don't know people well enough.

630
00:32:37,730 --> 00:32:40,030
First of all, Tian Jiatai

631
00:32:40,060 --> 00:32:42,850
claimed to recover the enemy property,

632
00:32:42,870 --> 00:32:45,870
but it's just a 50-50 joint venture
with the Japanese.

633
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:49,200
It's full cooperation
that funds and supports the enemy.

634
00:32:50,090 --> 00:32:50,810
Secondly,

635
00:32:51,230 --> 00:32:54,370
he supported Shao Ni, former President
of Shanghai General Chamber of Commerce,

636
00:32:54,370 --> 00:32:56,930
in taking a position in the puppet
Shanghai municipal government.

637
00:32:56,930 --> 00:33:00,710
He also plans to be the puppet government's
economic commissioner.

638
00:33:00,710 --> 00:33:02,440
How is that not being a traitor?

639
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:04,790
I don't understand all this nonsense.

640
00:33:04,790 --> 00:33:06,950
I only know he saved Master.

641
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:09,110
And he's still offering me food now.

642
00:33:09,460 --> 00:33:10,740
The Brigade Commander's wife reads to him,

643
00:33:10,740 --> 00:33:12,520
and she's earning his money.

644
00:33:12,540 --> 00:33:15,630
That's two different things.
You guys haven't betrayed the country

645
00:33:15,630 --> 00:33:17,360
or engaged in treasonous acts.

646
00:33:17,370 --> 00:33:18,700
That's certainly good.

647
00:33:19,020 --> 00:33:21,720
If, I mean if...

648
00:33:21,750 --> 00:33:24,480
If the Brigade Commander's wife
lost her chastity

649
00:33:24,480 --> 00:33:25,960
and had an affair with him,

650
00:33:26,090 --> 00:33:28,700
or even worse, participated in treason,

651
00:33:29,010 --> 00:33:31,070
then we would have to kill her as well.

652
00:33:31,410 --> 00:33:32,650
It won't come to that!

653
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:33,630
Listen,

654
00:33:33,650 --> 00:33:35,200
with me here,
it absolutely won't get to that point.

655
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:37,140
And it definitely won't
for the Brigade Commander's wife, either!

656
00:33:37,140 --> 00:33:39,870
Hey, can't you just talk to Mr. Tian...

657
00:33:41,380 --> 00:33:42,460
I mean, Tian.

658
00:33:42,610 --> 00:33:44,540
Can't you just talk him

659
00:33:44,570 --> 00:33:46,410
into switching sides

660
00:33:46,500 --> 00:33:49,010
and serving our side?

661
00:33:49,040 --> 00:33:50,060
You know what?

662
00:33:50,390 --> 00:33:52,150
Mr. Tian is very smart

663
00:33:52,170 --> 00:33:53,480
and educated.

664
00:33:53,870 --> 00:33:56,310
He gets along well
with the Brigade Commander's father,

665
00:33:56,310 --> 00:33:58,710
and he knows a lot
about classical Chinese.

666
00:34:00,610 --> 00:34:01,850
Wanfu,

667
00:34:02,810 --> 00:34:05,930
these educated people
you keep talking about are

668
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:09,489
exactly the most terrifying ones
once they betray the country.

669
00:34:09,659 --> 00:34:11,889
They are best at twisting truths.

670
00:34:14,070 --> 00:34:16,850
Do you know what it means
to be sanctimonious,

671
00:34:17,250 --> 00:34:19,179
what it means to feign compliance,

672
00:34:19,449 --> 00:34:21,850
or what it means
to wait for the highest bid?

673
00:34:23,139 --> 00:34:24,440
You don't need to know that much.

674
00:34:24,440 --> 00:34:26,840
This has already been decided
by the higher-ups.

675
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:28,370
I am responsible for the execution.

676
00:34:28,370 --> 00:34:30,300
You just need to help me execute it.

677
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:32,230
I... I...

678
00:34:32,250 --> 00:34:33,710
What do you want me to help you execute?

679
00:34:33,710 --> 00:34:34,480
Blindy, listen,

680
00:34:34,480 --> 00:34:36,210
I won't help you with anything.

681
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:38,960
What's with that look?

682
00:34:38,980 --> 00:34:40,340
Look at your creepy stare. You...

683
00:34:40,340 --> 00:34:42,100
Are you going to kill me, too?

684
00:34:58,750 --> 00:34:59,710
Wanfu,

685
00:35:00,240 --> 00:35:02,280
I believe you won't betray me.

686
00:35:05,230 --> 00:35:08,590
No rush.
I'll give you time to think about it.

687
00:35:09,340 --> 00:35:12,050
Come find me
when you've made up your mind.

688
00:35:12,710 --> 00:35:13,790
You may go back.

689
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:24,690
Blindy, I'm no more than a cook.

690
00:35:29,240 --> 00:35:31,910
You are still a soldier
of the 87th Brigade.

691
00:35:33,680 --> 00:35:35,680
Wash your face and rinse your mouth.

692
00:35:36,030 --> 00:35:38,360
Don't let anyone smell the alcohol on you.

693
00:35:55,110 --> 00:35:56,740
One brass pocket watch.

694
00:35:56,820 --> 00:35:57,860
Hello.

695
00:35:58,920 --> 00:36:01,030
One brass pocket watch.

696
00:36:02,390 --> 00:36:03,920
One women's cashmere coat.

697
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:08,210
One women's cashmere coat.

698
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:11,630
Manager Zhao, we already had a deal.

699
00:36:11,810 --> 00:36:13,710
How can you suddenly go back on your word?

700
00:36:13,710 --> 00:36:15,110
The charity sale is about to start.

701
00:36:15,110 --> 00:36:17,360
Where do you expect me to find a venue?

702
00:36:25,690 --> 00:36:26,490
What's wrong?

703
00:36:27,510 --> 00:36:29,280
A... A finger.

704
00:36:29,300 --> 00:36:31,460
What is going on?

705
00:36:34,070 --> 00:36:35,800
A trick played by the Japanese.

706
00:36:35,990 --> 00:36:38,480
They called
to threaten you yesterday, Miss.

707
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:40,440
Today, we're having a problem
with the venue.

708
00:36:40,440 --> 00:36:42,540
Now they've even escalated

709
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:44,410
to terrorist moves.

710
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:45,440
Yang,

711
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:48,440
call the police station and report this.

712
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:51,440
Comrades,

713
00:36:52,930 --> 00:36:56,270
let's continue with our own work.

714
00:36:56,300 --> 00:36:57,970
Don't be distracted by them.

715
00:36:58,550 --> 00:36:59,220
Go ahead.

716
00:37:01,210 --> 00:37:02,470
Let's get back to work.

717
00:37:04,930 --> 00:37:07,930
Yujiao, come with me.

718
00:37:16,970 --> 00:37:19,130
Are you afraid
of Japanese intelligence agents?

719
00:37:19,130 --> 00:37:20,190
No, I'm not afraid.

720
00:37:21,370 --> 00:37:24,080
Even face-to-face, I'm not afraid of them.

721
00:37:24,990 --> 00:37:26,800
Let me ask you a question.

722
00:37:28,320 --> 00:37:31,280
Do you know about the New Fourth Army?

723
00:37:36,110 --> 00:37:37,230
I know...

724
00:37:39,940 --> 00:37:42,870
It is an anti-Japanese force
of the Communist Party.

725
00:37:43,240 --> 00:37:45,550
The Army Commander is Ye Ting.

726
00:37:47,880 --> 00:37:50,600
The proceeds from our charity sale

727
00:37:51,030 --> 00:37:54,190
will not only go to the refugees nearby,

728
00:37:54,530 --> 00:37:58,970
but they will also be used
to buy winter clothes for the New Fourth Army.

729
00:38:00,690 --> 00:38:01,840
No wonder the Japanese

730
00:38:01,840 --> 00:38:03,500
hate the charity sale so much.

731
00:38:03,910 --> 00:38:05,850
Yes, recently,

732
00:38:06,510 --> 00:38:08,230
the Japanese intelligence agents
in the concession

733
00:38:08,230 --> 00:38:09,900
have been carrying out terrorist acts,

734
00:38:09,900 --> 00:38:14,630
like restraining the French Municipal Council
and the Shanghai Municipal Council.

735
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:18,170
They are trying to make
the people of Shanghai shut up.

736
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:20,420
But they have never killed off our passion

737
00:38:20,420 --> 00:38:22,550
for resisting the Japanese invasion.

738
00:38:22,630 --> 00:38:25,840
The Japanese also try to suppress us

739
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:27,800
to make an example of us.

740
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:29,840
So now,

741
00:38:30,230 --> 00:38:32,290
we should not only refuse to back down

742
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:34,230
but also make our charity sale

743
00:38:34,510 --> 00:38:37,760
even more successful and bustling.

744
00:38:41,180 --> 00:38:43,110
By the way, when you get home today,

745
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:44,880
thank Mr. Tian for me.

746
00:38:45,730 --> 00:38:46,790
Tian Jiatai?

747
00:38:46,880 --> 00:38:47,920
Yes.

748
00:38:53,030 --> 00:38:54,280
Actually, Mr. Tian is

749
00:38:54,300 --> 00:38:56,770
someone who does a lot

750
00:38:56,790 --> 00:38:58,920
but says very little.

751
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:02,530
When the Battle of Shanghai
just broke out,

752
00:39:03,110 --> 00:39:04,510
he led his workers

753
00:39:04,530 --> 00:39:06,700
to organize a rescue team for the wounded.

754
00:39:06,700 --> 00:39:09,840
He also made extra wards
for our field hospital.

755
00:39:09,860 --> 00:39:10,800
Later,

756
00:39:10,820 --> 00:39:12,420
when things got rough at the front,

757
00:39:12,420 --> 00:39:15,100
he donated a large batch of raincoats

758
00:39:15,750 --> 00:39:16,820
and medicine to us.

759
00:39:17,380 --> 00:39:19,900
After the Japanese Army
occupied the Chinese district,

760
00:39:19,900 --> 00:39:22,230
Mr. Tian didn't show up in person anymore.

761
00:39:22,330 --> 00:39:24,330
But he still anonymously

762
00:39:24,350 --> 00:39:26,150
donated to us

763
00:39:26,180 --> 00:39:28,650
over 10,000 yuan worth
of daily necessities,

764
00:39:28,650 --> 00:39:32,030
including some
for our charity sale this time.

765
00:39:40,630 --> 00:39:42,020
Master, I'm back.

766
00:39:42,560 --> 00:39:44,780
Yueming, look

767
00:39:44,810 --> 00:39:46,910
at the goodies I brought for you.

768
00:39:46,930 --> 00:39:48,450
I'll give you a long one.

769
00:39:48,470 --> 00:39:49,670
A long one. Very long.

770
00:39:51,400 --> 00:39:52,230
Eat up.

771
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:06,630
Wanfu.

772
00:40:07,430 --> 00:40:08,910
Why are you unhappy?

773
00:40:09,420 --> 00:40:11,020
Is something bothering you?

774
00:40:11,550 --> 00:40:12,590
Master,

775
00:40:13,780 --> 00:40:15,100
can you tell me

776
00:40:16,410 --> 00:40:18,220
what a traitor to China is?

777
00:40:19,040 --> 00:40:24,440
Those who turn to foreign races
to bully the Chinese are traitors.

778
00:40:24,740 --> 00:40:26,520
What if they haven't bullied Chinese?

779
00:40:26,520 --> 00:40:27,890
Do they still count as traitors to China?

780
00:40:27,890 --> 00:40:32,250
Working for the Japanese
when our two countries are at war

781
00:40:32,580 --> 00:40:34,240
makes them traitors to China.

782
00:40:35,830 --> 00:40:40,620
Then what kind of traitors
deserve to be killed?

783
00:40:47,850 --> 00:40:48,470
Let me do it. Let me.

784
00:40:48,470 --> 00:40:49,560
Master, I got this.

785
00:40:49,850 --> 00:40:50,650
Wanfu.

786
00:40:52,010 --> 00:40:53,320
There is a nice line

787
00:40:53,340 --> 00:40:55,480
in "Dream of the Red Chamber" that says,

788
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:57,480
"For a large and prosperous family,

789
00:40:57,520 --> 00:40:59,150
enemies from the outside

790
00:40:59,280 --> 00:41:01,360
can't bring it down quickly or easily.

791
00:41:01,360 --> 00:41:03,640
But if they destroy themselves
from within,

792
00:41:03,640 --> 00:41:05,640
they will cause the family
to fall completely."

793
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:07,510
If it weren't for the traitors to China,

794
00:41:07,510 --> 00:41:11,110
when the Japanese invaded like a snake
trying to swallow an elephant,

795
00:41:11,110 --> 00:41:13,310
they wouldn't have lasted long anyway.

796
00:41:13,410 --> 00:41:16,800
It was exactly
because of the traitors' help

797
00:41:16,870 --> 00:41:19,660
that they could establish
a puppet government,

798
00:41:19,680 --> 00:41:22,310
turning our China into a vassal.

799
00:41:22,580 --> 00:41:25,140
Such traitors deserve to die!

800
00:41:32,910 --> 00:41:35,240
Why did you bring this up?

801
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:44,350
Master.

802
00:41:44,770 --> 00:41:46,700
Today, I heard them say

803
00:41:46,980 --> 00:41:49,540
that a wealthy merchant
in the International Settlement was

804
00:41:49,540 --> 00:41:51,630
assassinated by Anti-Japanese elements.

805
00:41:51,630 --> 00:41:55,710
The flyers said
he did business with the Japanese,

806
00:41:55,740 --> 00:41:57,940
bankrolling and supporting the enemy.

807
00:42:03,090 --> 00:42:07,920
So you're worried about Mr. Tian?

808
00:42:12,030 --> 00:42:15,340
Mr. Tian already explained to me.

809
00:42:15,900 --> 00:42:18,530
He is fighting against the Japanese.

810
00:42:18,560 --> 00:42:20,760
There are international conventions.

811
00:42:21,140 --> 00:42:22,580
But the Japanese

812
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:27,440
have even seized
private factory properties.

813
00:42:27,460 --> 00:42:29,990
Mr. Tian is arguing based on reason

814
00:42:30,020 --> 00:42:31,940
to get his own factory back.

815
00:42:31,960 --> 00:42:33,820
There's nothing wrong with that.

816
00:42:34,340 --> 00:42:37,570
Yes, he is fighting the Japanese.

817
00:42:37,800 --> 00:42:39,400
But in the eyes of outsiders,

818
00:42:39,690 --> 00:42:42,150
he has such close and frequent dealings
with the Japanese.

819
00:42:42,150 --> 00:42:42,980
Not to mention outsiders,

820
00:42:42,980 --> 00:42:45,540
even we found his stance hard to tell.

821
00:42:47,680 --> 00:42:51,470
That is exactly Mr. Tian's predicament.

822
00:42:53,920 --> 00:42:54,840
Look,

823
00:42:54,960 --> 00:42:56,480
the Japanese are

824
00:42:56,550 --> 00:42:59,310
blatantly trampling
on international conventions

825
00:42:59,310 --> 00:43:01,320
to seize whatever they want
by trickery or force.

826
00:43:01,320 --> 00:43:04,120
Someone has to step up
and speak out, right?
